abstract.text: Construct and manage a graphical, event-driven user interface for your iOS, iPadOS, or tvOS app.
Information about a print job that the system uses when it prints.
Specifies that the printed content consists of mixed text, graphics, and images. The default paper is Letter, A4, or similar locale-specific designation. Output is normal quality, duplex.

Specifies that the printed content is grayscale. Set the output type to this value when your printable content contains no color—for example, it’s black text only. The default paper is Letter/A4. Output is grayscale quality, duplex. This content type can produce a performance improvement in some cases.
Specifies that the printed content consists of black-and-white or color images. The default paper is 4x6, A6, or similar locale-specific designation. Output is high quality, simplex.
The kind of printable content.
A user interface that manages the printing of documents, images, and other printable content in iOS.
An optional set of methods that the delegate of the shared print-interaction controller implements.
Asks the delegate for an object that encapsulates the paper size and printing area for the print job.
An object that draws pages of content to print, with or without the assistance of print formatters.
The size of the paper for printing.
The size of paper for a print job and the rectangular area that the content prints within.
The print-paper object that UIKit determines to be the best for a print job based on the specified page size and the paper size–imageable area combinations specific to the printer.
The size of the sheet to use for printing.
Deprecated.
The rectangle that represents the portion of the paper that can be imaged upon.
A printer on the network.
